05713nam a22009135i 9783035618310DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20192020sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2019944758  a97830356183107 a10.1515/97830356183102doi  a(DE-B1597)502064  a(OCoLC)1125186876  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH00aHT169.M62bM499 2019 7aARC0100002bisacsh1 avon Wissel, Christian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aDwelling Urbanism :bCity Making through Corporeal Practice in Mexico City /cChristian von Wissel. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2019] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (208 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aBauwelt Fundamente ;v16600tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- t1. Infrastructural Practice and the Making of City -- t2. Citying, Mexico City and Studying the Practice of City Making -- t3. Providing Lives -- t4. Growing Houses -- t5. Riding the Highway -- t6. City Making through Corporeal Practice -- tReferences0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aCity dwellers are direct agents in the making of cities; yet how do they actually constitute and sustain the urban and its forms? How do they practice the urban and through this practice shape the city-in-the-making that emerges along with them on the backs of their working bodies? Dwelling Urbanism re-thinks the urban from this perspective of corporeal making and with regard to the cityness that it bears. It delves into the thick of life in the periphery of Mexico City, uncovering the everyday actions and efforts that practitioners of space accomplish when building houses, creating jobs and putting themselves to work as infrastructure. How are consequential conjunctions, how is access to, and presence in the city actively grown? And what does such thinking the city as a verb, as citying, imply for urban planning?  aStadtbewohner sind aktiv an der Gestaltung ihrer urbanen Umwelt beteiligt, aber wie organisieren und sichern sie diese Aktivitäten und deren Materialisierung in städtischen Formen? Wie prägen sie die „Stadt-im-Werden", die mit ihnen und auf ihren Schultern täglich neu entsteht? "City Making" reflektiert unser Verständnis von Stadt aus der Perspektive körperlichen Handelns und der „cityness", die es hervorbringt. Das Buch dringt in das Leben an der Peripherie von Mexico-City ein und beschreibt die körperliche Arbeit, mit der „Raumpraktiker" dort Häuser bauen, Arbeitsplätze schaffen und sich selbst als Infrastruktur einbringen. So werden die folgenreichen Verbindungen, die sie knüpfen, zum stadtgenerierenden Faktor – mit weitreichenden Konsequenzen für die Art und Weise,wie wir unsere Städte zukünftig denken und planen wollen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity and town lifezMexicozMexico City. 0aCity planningzMexicozMexico City. 0aUrbanizationzMexicozMexico City. 4aMexico City. 4aUrbanismus. 7aARCHITECTURE / Urban & Land Use Planning.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2019z9783110605747oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG0 cEPUBz97830356182350 cprintz97